jcolibri.extensions.textual.method
Class PartofSpeechMethod

java.lang.Object
  jcolibri.cbrcore.CBRMethod
      jcolibri.extensions.textual.method.PartofSpeechMethod
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, CBRTerm
public class PartofSpeechMethod
extends CBRMethod

This method uses a Maximum Entropy tagger (Opennlp) to assign Part-of-Speech tags.

Tags are stored in Tokens using the Tokens.POSSTAG parameter

Possible values are:

  • 1. CC Coordinating conjunction
  • 2. CD Cardinal number
  • 3. DT Determiner
  • 4. EX Existential there
  • 5. FW Foreign word
  • 6. IN Preposition or subordinating conjunction
  • 7. JJ Adjective
  • 8. JJR Adjective, comparative
  • 9. JJS Adjective, superlative
  • 10. LS List item marker
  • 11. MD Modal
  • 12. NN Noun, singular or mass
  • 13. NNS Noun, plural
  • 14. NNP Proper noun, singular
  • 15. NNPS Proper noun, plural
  • 16. PDT Predeterminer
  • 17. POS Possessive ending
  • 18. PRP Personal pronoun
  • 19. PRP$ Possessive pronoun
  • 20. RB Adverb
  • 21. RBR Adverb, comparative
  • 22. RBS Adverb, superlative
  • 23. RP Particle
  • 24. SYM Symbol
  • 25. TO to
  • 26. UH Interjection
  • 27. VB Verb, base form
  • 28. VBD Verb, past tense
  • 29. VBG Verb, gerund or present participle
  • 30. VBN Verb, past participle
  • 31. VBP Verb, non-3rd person singular present
  • 32. VBZ Verb, 3rd person singular present
  • 33. WDT Wh-determiner
  • 34. WP Wh-pronoun
  • 35. WP$ Possessive wh-pronoun
  • 36. WRB Wh-adverb

Developed at: Robert Gordon University - Aberdeen & Facultad Informática, Universidad Complutense de Madrid (GAIA)
